---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Business Loan Interest Rates - Compare All Banks 2026 | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Business Loan Interest Rates</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Business Loan Interest Rates</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Compare business loan interest rates across leading banks, NBFCs, and government-backed schemes in India. Find rates starting from 10.50% p.a. for established businesses and startups. Updated for April 2026.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Lowest Rate: 10.50% p.a.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-building-columns"></i>
          <span>50+ Lenders Compared</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-clock"></i>
          <span>Updated: April 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>Business Loan Interest Rates in India — April 2026</h2>
          <p>Business loan interest rates in India range from 10.50% to 30% p.a. depending on the lender type, business vintage, annual turnover, credit history, and loan amount. Nationalized banks like SBI and Bank of Baroda offer the lowest rates for established businesses with strong financials, while NBFCs and fintech lenders provide faster approvals for newer businesses at moderately higher rates.</p>
          <p>At TrueCred Loan Expert, we aggregate business loan rates from over 50 banks, NBFCs, and government schemes daily to help business owners make the best borrowing decision. Whether you need working capital, equipment financing, or expansion funding, choosing the right lender based on your business profile can save you ₹1,00,000 to ₹5,00,000 over the loan tenure. Our experts also guide you through MUDRA, CGTMSE, and other subsidized schemes that offer concessional rates.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">10.50%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Lowest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹75 Lakh</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Unsecured Loan</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">50+</span>
              <span class="info-label">Lenders Compared</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Business Loan Interest Rate Comparison — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>11.25% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 1.50%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Bank</td>
                <td>11.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.50%</td>
                <td>4 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>12.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.00%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bajaj Finserv</td>
                <td>10.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 3.00%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Lendingkart</td>
                <td>13.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.50%</td>
                <td>3 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business vintage of at least 2 years (1 year for some NBFCs)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum annual turnover of ₹10,00,000 for unsecured business loans</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business owner aged between 25 and 65 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 700+ (personal) and CMR score of 6 or below (business)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> GST registration and ITR filing for at least 2 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Profitable business with positive cash flow as per financial statements</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Get the Best Business Loan Rate</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Assess Your Needs</h4>
              <p>Determine the loan amount, purpose, and preferred tenure. Business loans are available for working capital, expansion, equipment, and more.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Compare Lenders</h4>
              <p>Use TrueCred to compare interest rates, processing fees, and terms across 50+ lenders tailored to your business type and turnover.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Prepare Financials</h4>
              <p>Organize your ITR, GST returns, bank statements, and profit & loss statements. Strong financials unlock the lowest rates.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Apply & Get Funded</h4>
              <p>Submit your application with all required documents. Fast-track approval available for businesses with turnover above ₹50 lakhs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business registration documents — GST certificate, Shop Act license, or incorporation certificate</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Last 2 years ITR with computation of income and balance sheet</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Last 12 months bank statements of the business account</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Latest GST returns (GSTR-1 and GSTR-3B) for the past 12 months</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> KYC documents of all directors/partners — Aadhaar, PAN, and address proof</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Proof of business address — utility bill, rent agreement, or property documents</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Get Business Loan Quote</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="200000">₹2,00,000</option>
                  <option value="500000">₹5,00,000</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                  <option value="2000000">₹20,00,000</option>
                  <option value="3000000">₹30,00,000</option>
                  <option value="5000000">₹50,00,000</option>
                  <option value="7500000">₹75,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about business loan interest rates.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What is the cheapest business loan available in India?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Government-backed schemes like MUDRA Shishu (up to ₹50,000) offer the lowest rates at around 7-8% p.a. For unsecured business loans, Bajaj Finserv starts at 10.50% for established businesses. SBI offers 11.25% with CGTMSE guarantee. The rate you get depends on business vintage, turnover, and credit profile.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Which type of business loan has the lowest interest rate?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Secured business loans (against property or FD) have the lowest rates, starting from 8.75% p.a. Among unsecured options, government-subsidized schemes offer the best rates. Term loans for asset purchase are generally cheaper than working capital or overdraft facilities. Newer digital lenders may charge higher rates but offer faster processing.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can a new business get a loan at competitive rates?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              New businesses (less than 2 years old) can access loans through MUDRA scheme (up to ₹10 lakh at 9-12% p.a.), startup loans from select NBFCs, and collateral-backed business loans. Without collateral or government guarantee, rates for new businesses typically range from 16-24% p.a. Building a strong GST filing history helps secure better rates.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How is the interest rate on a business loan calculated?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Business loan rates are determined by: business vintage (older = better), annual turnover and profitability, personal and business credit scores, industry sector risk, loan amount and tenure, collateral (if any), existing banking relationship, and GST compliance history. Lenders use a combination of these factors in their credit models.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Should I choose a fixed or floating rate for my business loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              It depends on your cash flow predictability needs. Fixed rates provide consistent EMIs, making financial planning easier — ideal for businesses with stable revenue. Floating rates may start lower and benefit from future rate cuts but carry the risk of EMI increases. For short-tenure loans (1-3 years), fixed rates are generally preferred; for longer tenures, floating rates may save more if interest rates decline.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Get the Best Business Loan Rate for Your Company</h3>
          <p>Compare rates from 50+ lenders and save up to ₹5 lakhs in interest. Free comparison, instant results.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
